{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"95f095cd-15d5-4597-9f6e-f41291af17dd","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n**MSTest**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**xUnit**\n```csharp\n[Fact(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n// or for theories:\n[Theory(Skip = \"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**NUnit**\n```csharp\n[Ignore(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\n**TUnit**\n```csharp\n[Skip(\"Reason for skipping\")]\n```\n\nAll four will mark the test as skipped/ignored in test results rather than removing it entirely, so you retain visibility that the test exists but isn't running.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6a3f593b-099d-47c7-b449-25b123a82229","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct attribute syntax to skip/ignore tests with a reason message in four .NET test frameworks: MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. This is a knowledge question I can answer directly without needing tools.","outputTokens":227,"requestId":"E3D7:3B2241:557C88:62C5DA:6A0523D6"},"id":"c1638784-bb2a-4364-a1e6-41e6751bbf4f","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:22:35.853Z","parentId":"1f6da78e-6889-4bec-928f-3d113388c038"}
